-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party software
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

This software depends on third-party libraries that are distributed under
their own license terms. A full enumeration of every direct and
transitive dependency — across compile, runtime, provided and test
scopes — is generated by the build into THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.txt at the
root of the repository. Regenerate with:

    ./mvnw license:aggregate-add-third-party

License families observed in the current dependency tree:

  - Apache License 2.0          (AssertJ, Byte Buddy, apiguardian,
                                 opentest4j)
  - MIT                         (the Cucumber stack)
  - EPL 2.0                     (JUnit Platform)
  - LGPL                        (JFreeChart)

The four core library modules — commons, heerwisch-api, frau-holle and
nachtkrapp — are JDK-only and pull in no third-party runtime code; their
only non-test dependencies are sibling 0BSD modules of this repository.

JFreeChart is the only LGPL-only dependency and the only third-party
runtime dependency in the repository — it is used solely by the
heerwisch-jfreechart driver module. It is linked dynamically as a Maven
artifact, so downstream consumers retain their LGPL right to replace it
without having to re-license this project. Consumers that do not need
chart rendering can depend on the other modules and never pull it in.

See THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.txt for the exhaustive list and project URLs.
